{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884306324,"sessionID":"ses_2850cab71ffe5dB8FyygvpNmyl","part":{"id":"prt_d7af3f78f001phq2QPiGfqhAPR","messageID":"msg_d7af3e12c001DZok9SYFQaiRgb","sessionID":"ses_2850cab71ffe5dB8FyygvpNmyl","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-b0bd415206064402aa16e9f396723960","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 Implementation Plan\n2: \n3: **Feature:** AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n4: **Goal:** Implement the AgentRuntimeClient in the AgentCube Python SDK, providing a streamlined interface for invoking agent runtime workloads through the Router service with proper session management.\n5: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n6: - AgentRuntimeClient provides high-level API for agent runtime interactions\n7: - Session ID is bootstrapped from Router or reused from existing session\n8: - Context manager support ensures proper resource cleanup\n9: - Invoke method handles HTTP communication via Router with proper timeout configuration\n10: - Connection pooling is implemented via requests.Session\n11: - Error handling includes session validation and HTTP error propagation\n12: - Unit tests achieve >80% code coverage\n13: - Integration tests work with real Router service\n14: **Architecture:** Python SDK client with AgentRuntimeClient (main API) and AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (HTTP layer), following context manager pattern for resource cleanup.\n15: **Tech Stack:** Python 3.10+, requests ^2.31.0\n16: **Frontend validation:** No\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ### Task 1: Verify AgentRuntimeClient class structure\n21: \n22: **Files:**\n23: - Verify: `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n24: - Verify: `agentcube/__init__.py`\n25: \n26: **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n27: \n28: ```python\n29: # tests/test_agent_runtime_client_structure.py\n30: import pytest\n31: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n32: \n33: \n34: def test_agent_runtime_client_has_required_methods():\n35:     \"\"\"Verify AgentRuntimeClient has all required public methods.\"\"\"\n36:     required_methods = [\n37:         \"__init__\",\n38:         \"__enter__\",\n39:         \"__exit__\",\n40:         \"invoke\",\n41:         \"close\",\n42:     ]\n43: \n44:     for method_name in required_methods:\n45:         assert hasattr(AgentRuntimeClient, method_name), f\"AgentRuntimeClient missing method: {method_name}\"\n46: \n47: \n48: def test_agent_runtime_client_has_required_attributes():\n49:     \"\"\"Verify AgentRuntimeClient has all required instance attributes.\"\"\"\n50:     with pytest.mock.patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"):\n51:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n52:             agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n53:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n54:         )\n55: \n56:     required_attributes = [\n57:         \"agent_name\",\n58:         \"namespace\",\n59:         \"timeout\",\n60:         \"connect_timeout\",\n61:         \"logger\",\n62:         \"router_url\",\n63:         \"session_id\",\n64:         \"dp_client\",\n65:         \"verbose\",\n66:     ]\n67: \n68:     for attr in required_attributes:\n69:         assert hasattr(client, attr), f\"AgentRuntimeClient missing attribute: {attr}\"\n70: \n71:     client.close()\n72: ```\n73: \n74: **Step 2: Run test to verify it passes**\n75: \n76: Run: `python -m pytest tests/test_agent_runtime_client_structure.py -v`\n77: Expected: PASS\n78: \n79: **Step 3: Verify AgentRuntimeClient is exported**\n80: \n81: ```python\n82: # tests/test_public_api.py\n83: import agentcube\n84: \n85: \n86: def test_agent_runtime_client_exported():\n87:     \"\"\"Verify AgentRuntimeClient is exported from agentcube package.\"\"\"\n88:     assert hasattr(agentcube, \"AgentRuntimeClient\")\n89:     assert \"AgentRuntimeClient\" in agentcube.__all__\n90: ```\n91: \n92: **Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n93: \n94: Run: `python -m pytest tests/test_public_api.py -v`\n95: Expected: PASS\n96: \n97: **Step 5: Commit**\n98: \n99: ```bash\n100: git add tests/test_agent_runtime_client_structure.py tests/test_public_api.py\n101: git commit -m \"test(ar-028): verify AgentRuntimeClient class structure\"\n102: ```\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ### Task 2: Verify AgentRuntimeClient initialization with all parameters\n107: \n108: **Files:**\n109: - Verify: `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n110: - Modify: `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py`\n111: \n112: **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n113: \n114: ```python\n115: # tests/test_agent_runtime_client_initialization.py\n116: import os\n117: from unittest.mock import patch\n118: import pytest\n119: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n120: \n121: \n122: def test_initialization_with_all_parameters():\n123:     \"\"\"Test AgentRuntimeClient initialization with all parameters.\"\"\"\n124:     with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n125:         mock_dp_instance = mock_dp.return_value\n126:         mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session\"\n127: \n128:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n129:             agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n130:             namespace=\"production\",\n131:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n132:             verbose=True,\n133:             session_id=\"existing-session\",\n134:             timeout=180,\n135:             connect_timeout=10.0,\n136:         )\n137: \n138:         assert client.agent_name == \"my-agent\"\n139:         assert client.namespace == \"production\"\n140:         assert client.router_url == \"http://router:8080\"\n141:         assert client.verbose is True\n142:         assert client.session_id == \"existing-session\"\n143:         assert client.timeout == 180\n144:         assert client.connect_timeout == 10.0\n145: \n146:         # Verify bootstrap_session_id was NOT called when session_id is provided\n147:         mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.assert_not_called()\n148: \n149:         client.close()\n150: \n151: \n152: def test_initialization_defaults():\n153:     \"\"\"Test AgentRuntimeClient initialization with default values.\"\"\"\n154:     with patch.dict(os.environ, {\"ROUTER_URL\": \"http://router:8080\"}):\n155:         with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n156:             mock_dp_instance = mock_dp.return_value\n157:             mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session\"\n158: \n159:             client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")\n160: \n161:             assert client.agent_name == \"my-agent\"\n162:             assert client.namespace == \"default\"\n163:             assert client.router_url == \"http://router:8080\"\n164:             assert client.verbose is False\n165:             assert client.timeout == 120\n166:             assert client.connect_timeout == 5.0\n167: \n168:             # Verify bootstrap_session_id was called when session_id is NOT provided\n169:             mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.assert_called_once()\n170: \n171:             client.close()\n172: \n173: \n174: def test_initialization_without_router_url_and_env():\n175:     \"\"\"Test AgentRuntimeClient initialization without router_url or env var.\"\"\"\n176:     with patch.dict(os.environ, {}, clear=True):\n177:         with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n178:             mock_dp_instance = mock_dp.return_value\n179:             mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session\"\n180: \n181:             client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")\n182: \n183:             assert client.router_url == \"\"\n184:             assert client.logger.warning.called\n185: \n186:             client.close()\n187: ```\n188: \n189: **Step 2: Run test to verify it passes**\n190: \n191: Run: `python -m pytest tests/test_agent_runtime_client_initialization.py -v`\n192: Expected: PASS\n193: \n194: **Step 3: Commit**\n195: \n196: ```bash\n197: git add tests/test_agent_runtime_client_initialization.py\n198: git commit -m \"test(ar-028): verify AgentRuntimeClient initialization\"\n199: ```\n200: \n201: ---\n202: \n203: ### Task 3: Verify AgentRuntimeClient context manager support\n204: \n205: **Files:**\n206: - Verify: `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n207: - Modify: `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py`\n208: \n209: **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n210: \n211: ```python\n212: # tests/test_agent_runtime_client_context_manager.py\n213: import pytest\n214: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n215: \n216: \n217: def test_context_manager_enter_returns_self():\n218:     \"\"\"Test __enter__ returns self.\"\"\"\n219:     with pytest.mock.patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"):\n220:         with AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\") as client:\n221:             assert isinstance(client, AgentRuntimeClient)\n222: \n223: \n224: def test_context_manager_exit_calls_close():\n225:     \"\"\"Test __exit__ calls close method.\"\"\"\n226:     with pytest.mock.patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"):\n227:         with pytest.mock.patch.object(AgentRuntimeClient, \"close\") as mock_close:\n228:             with AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\"):\n229:                 pass\n230: \n231:             mock_close.assert_called_once()\n232: \n233: \n234: def test_context_manager_exit_calls_close_on_exception():\n235:     \"\"\"Test __exit__ calls close method even when exception occurs.\"\"\"\n236:     with pytest.mock.patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"):\n237:         with pytest.mock.patch.object(AgentRuntimeClient, \"close\") as mock_close:\n238:             with pytest.raises(ValueError):\n239:                 with AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\"):\n240:                     raise ValueError(\"Test error\")\n241: \n242:             mock_close.assert_called_once()\n243: \n244: \n245: def test_close_is_idempotent():\n246:     \"\"\"Test close can be called multiple times without error.\"\"\"\n247:     with pytest.mock.patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"):\n248:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\")\n249: \n250:         # First close\n251:         client.close()\n252: \n253:         # Second close should not raise\n254:         client.close()\n255: ```\n256: \n257: **Step 2: Run test to verify it passes**\n258: \n259: Run: `python -m pytest tests/test_agent_runtime_client_context_manager.py -v`\n260: Expected: PASS\n261: \n262: **Step 3: Commit**\n263: \n264: ```bash\n265: git add tests/test_agent_runtime_client_context_manager.py\n266: git commit -m \"test(ar-028): verify AgentRuntimeClient context manager support\"\n267: ```\n268: \n269: ---\n270: \n271: ### Task 4: Verify AgentRuntimeClient invoke method\n272: \n273: **Files:**\n274: - Verify: `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n275: - Modify: `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py`\n276: \n277: **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n278: \n279: ```python\n280: # tests/test_agent_runtime_client_invoke.py\n281: import pytest\n282: from unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch\n283: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n284: \n285: \n286: def test_invoke_success():\n287:     \"\"\"Test invoke method with successful response.\"\"\"\n288:     with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n289:         mock_dp_instance = mock_dp.return_value\n290:         mock_dp_instance.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"test-session-id\"\n291: \n292:         mock_response = MagicMock()\n293:         