guration (pytest.ini)\n- [ ] Support test discovery (tests/ directory)\n- [ ] Create `test-python-unit` target for unit tests only\n- [ ] Create `test-python-integration` target for integration tests\n- [ ] Test Python SDK tests\n- [ ] Test CLI tests (if applicable)\n\n**Verification**: Python tests run successfully with coverage reporting\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Implement integration test targets\n- [ ] Create `test-integration` target for all integration tests\n- [ ] Create `test-integration-go` for Go integration tests\n- [ ] Create `test-integration-python` for Python integration tests\n- [ ] Support environment configuration for integration tests\n- [ ] Support test data setup and teardown\n- [ ] Add integration test timeout configuration\n- [ ] Create `test-e2e` target for end-to-end tests\n- [ ] Support running integration tests against local environment\n- [ ] Support running integration tests against remote environment\n- [ ] Test integration test execution\n- [ ] Verify test isolation and cleanup\n\n**Verification**: Integration tests run successfully with proper setup and teardown\n\n---\n\n### Task 10: Implement test report targets\n- [ ] Create `test-report` target to generate all test reports\n- [ ] Create `test-report-go` for Go test reports\n- [ ] Create `test-report-python` for Python test reports\n- [ ] Generate HTML coverage reports for Go\n- [ ] Generate HTML coverage reports for Python\n- [ ] Generate combined test summary\n- [ ] Store reports in REPORT_DIR\n- [ ] Support report cleanup (`clean-reports`)\n- [ ] Test report generation\n- [ ] Verify report accuracy\n\n**Verification**: Comprehensive test reports are generated for all test types\n\n---\n\n### Task 11: Implement Go lint targets\n- [ ] Create `lint-go` target to run Go linters\n- [ ] Use gofmt for code formatting checks\n- [ ] Use go vet for static analysis\n- [ ] Use golangci-lint if available\n- [ ] Create `lint-go-fix` target to auto-fix linting issues\n- [ ] Support lint configurat